[2026-03-18T18:50:02.876Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\n\n## REQUIREMENT\n\n# Wildcard event type subscriptions\n\n## Metadata\n- **Category**: functionality\n- **Effort**: High (3/3)\n- **Impact**: Unknown (7/3)\n- **Scan Type**: feature_scout\n- **Generated**: 3/18/2026, 7:14:44 PM\n\n## Description\nExtend subscription matching in bus.ts to support wildcard patterns in eventType (e.g. gitlab_* matches gitlab_push, gitlab_merge_request). Add an is_pattern boolean flag to subscriptions. During matching, getSubscriptionsByEventType would also fetch pattern subscriptions and evaluate them with the same prefix-matching logic already used for sourceFilter. Inspired by NATS subject wildcards and RabbitMQ topic exchange routing keys.\n\n## Reasoning\nCurrently each subscription is tied to one exact eventType. To react to all GitLab events, a user must create separate subscriptions for each type. Wildcard subscriptions are standard in every mature event system and dramatically reduce subscription management overhead. The prefix-wildcard matching code already exists in sourceFilterMatches � reusing it for eventType is low-effort.\n\n\n## Recommended Skills\n\nUse Claude Code skills as appropriate for implementation guidance. Check `.claude/skills/` directory for available skills.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\n\n## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\n\n- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\n- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\n- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\n\n## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. Log your implementation using the `log_implementation` MCP tool with:\n   - requirementName: the requirement filename (without .md)\n   - title: 2-6 word summary\n   - overview: 1-2 paragraphs describing what was done\n   - category: one of feature/bugfix/refactor/performance/security/infrastructure/ui/docs/test\n   - patternsApplied: comma-separated patterns used (e.g. \"repository pattern, debounce, memoization\")\n\n2. Verify: `npx tsc --noEmit` (fix any type errors)\n\nBegin implementation now."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"15915e67-0f08-45e6-a989-69b2c8df5088","uuid":"0421b4cd-d6e8-40a1-9e23-ced96ecabdd0","timestamp":"2026-03-18T18:50:02.786Z","isSynthetic":true}
