[2026-03-18T18:51:12.449Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01G392R7jPGR2USL7R4bPHor","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the codebase exploration.\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Summary\n\nI've thoroughly explored the personas-cloud codebase. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **bus.ts - Event Matching System**\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/.claude/worktrees/idempotent-mapping-emerson/packages/shared/src/bus.ts`\n\nThe bus.ts file is a lightweight event matching engine ported from the desktop engine (engine/bus.rs). Key components:\n\n**EventMatch Interface:**\n- Represents an event matched to a persona subscription that should execute\n- Contains: eventId, eventType, subscriptionId, personaId, payload, sourceId, useCaseId\n\n**matchEvent() Function (lines 26-47):**\n- Core matching logic that filters subscriptions against an event\n- Returns array of EventMatch objects\n- Applies 4 matching rules:\n  1. subscription.eventType must equal event.eventType\n  2. If subscription.sourceFilter is set, event.sourceId must match\n  3. If event.targetPersonaId is set, only that persona's subscriptions match\n  4. subscription.enabled must be true\n\n**sourceFilterMatches() Function (lines 53-61):**\n- Simple exact match or prefix wildcard matching\n- If filter ends with `*`, performs prefix match: `sourceId.startsWith(prefix)`\n- Otherwise, exact string equality: `sourceId === filter`\n- Returns false if sourceId is null\n\n### 2. **Subscription Model & Type Definitions**\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/.claude/worktrees/idempotent-mapping-emerson/packages/shared/src/types.ts`\n\n**PersonaEventSubscription Interface (lines 87-96):**\n```typescript\n{\n  id: string;\n  personaId: string;\n  eventType: string;\n  sourceFilter: string | null;  // Supports exact or wildcard (e.g., \"gitlab/*\")\n  enabled: boolean;\n  useCaseId: string | null;\n  createdAt: string;\n  updatedAt: string;\n}\n```\n\n**PersonaEvent Interface (lines 72-85):**\n- Represents an event in the system\n- Contains: id, projectId, eventType, sourceType, sourceId, targetPersonaId, payload, status, errorMessage, processedAt, useCaseId, createdAt\n\n### 3. **getSubscriptionsByEventType() Function**\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/.claude/worktrees/idempotent-mapping-emerson/packages/orchestrator/src/db.ts` (lines 549-556)\n\n```typescript\nexport function getSubscriptionsByEventType(\n  db: Database.Database, \n  eventType: string, \n  projectId?: string\n): PersonaEventSubscription[]\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Queries all subscriptions matching a specific eventType\n- Supports optional projectId filtering for multi-tenant isolation\n- Uses SQL: `SELECT * FROM persona_event_subscriptions WHERE event_type = ? AND project_id = ?`\n- Returns array of PersonaEventSubscription objects\n\n**Called by:** eventProcessor.ts line 46\n\n### 4. **Database/Storage Layer - Drizzle & better-sqlite3**\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/.claude/worktrees/idempotent-mapping-emerson/packages/orchestrator/src/db.ts`\n\n**Database:** better-sqlite3 (SQLite with WAL mode)\n\n**persona_event_subscriptions Table Schema (lines 145-155):**\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_event_subscriptions (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES personas(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  event_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n  source_filter TEXT,\n  enabled INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,\n  use_case_id TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n)\n```\n\n**Related Tables:**\n- persona_events: stores event records with status tracking\n- personas: persona configuration\n- persona_event_subscriptions: subscriptions (the core link)\n\n**Key DB Functions:**\n- `createSubscription()` (lines 527-537): Creates new subscriptions\n- `getSubscriptionsByEventType()` (lines 549-556): Retrieves subscriptions by event type\n- `listSubscriptionsForPersona()` (lines 544-547): Gets all subscriptions for a persona\n- `updateSubscription()` (lines 558-573): Updates subscription settings\n- `deleteSubscription()` (lines 575-577): Deletes a subscription\n\n### 5. **How Subscriptions Are Created - API Routes**\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/.claude/worktrees/idempotent-mapping-emerson/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts` (lines 160-177)\n\n**POST /api/subscriptions** (lines 160-164):\n- Creates new event subscription\n- Request body fields: personaId, eventType, sourceFilter (optional), enabled (default true), useCaseId (optional), projectId (auto-set for users)\n- Calls: `db.createSubscription(database, body)`\n- Returns: 201 with PersonaEventSubscription object\n\n**PUT /api/subscriptions/{id}** (lines 165-170):\n- Updates existing subscription\n- Request body: { eventType?, sourceFilter?, enabled? }\n- Calls: `db.updateSubscription(database, id, body)`\n- Returns: 200 with updated subscription\n\n**DELETE /api/subscriptions/{id}** (lines 171-174):\n- Deletes a subscription\n- Returns: 200 { deleted: true }\n\n**GET /api/personas/{id}/subscriptions** (lines 175-177):\n- Lists all subscriptions for a persona\n- Returns: 200 with array of subscriptions\n\n### 6. **Event Processing Flow**\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/.claude/worktrees/idempotent-mapping-emerson/packages/orchestrator/src/eventProcessor.ts`\n\n**startEventProcessor() (lines 16-31):**\n- Starts a 2-second tick interval (configurable, default 2000ms)\n- Calls eventBusTick() repeatedly\n\n**eventBusTick() (lines 33-123):**\nMain event processing loop:\n1. Fetches up to 50 pending events: `db.getPendingEvents(database, 50)`\n2. For each event:\n   - Marks event as 'processing'\n   - Gets subscriptions by event type: `db.getSubscriptionsByEventType(database, event.eventType, event.projectId)`\n   - Matches event to subscriptions: `matchEvent(event, subs)` (from bus.ts)\n   - For each match:\n     - Checks persona exists and is enabled\n     - Checks concurrency limits\n     - Parses event payload as JSON\n     - Assembles prompt from persona config and tools\n     - Creates ExecRequest and submits to dispatcher\n   - Updates event status: delivered/partial/failed/skipped\n\n### 7. **File Structure & Packages**\n\n**@dac-cloud/shared** - Shared types and utilities:\n- `bus.ts`: Event matching engine\n- `types.ts`: Domain type definitions\n- `protocol.ts`: WebSocket protocol between orchestrator and workers\n- `prompt.ts`: Prompt assembly for personas\n- `crypto.ts`: Encryption utilities\n\n**@dac-cloud/orchestrator** - Main orchestration service:\n- `index.ts`: Main entry point, starts all services\n- `db.ts`: SQLite database layer with schema and CRUD operations\n- `eventProcessor.ts`: Event bus tick loop\n- `dispatcher.ts`: Execution queuing and worker pool coordination\n- `httpApi.ts`: HTTP REST API server\n- `workerPool.ts`: WebSocket pool for worker processes\n- `kafka.ts`: Kafka client for event streaming\n- `tokenManager.ts`: Claude API token management\n- `oauth.ts`: OAuth flow for Anthropic subscriptions\n- `auth.ts`: Request authentication\n- `triggerScheduler.ts`: Scheduled trigger execution\n\n**@dac-cloud/worker** - Worker processes:\n- Executes persona prompts via Claude\n- Emits events back to orchestrator\n\n### 8. **Event Lifecycle**\n\n1. **Event Creation**: POST /api/events creates event with status='pending'\n2. **Event Processing**: eventBusTick picks up pending events every 2 seconds\n3. **Subscription Matching**: Gets subscriptions by eventType, filters by sourceFilter\n4. **Execution Dispatch**: Creates ExecRequest for each matched subscription\n5. **Status Updates**: Event status becomes delivered/partial/failed/skipped\n6. **Event Consumption**: Workers can emit events that cycle back through the system\n\n### 9. **Key Integration Points**\n\n**Event → Subscription Matching Chain:**\n1. Event arrives via API or Kafka (persona.events.v1 topic)\n2. eventProcessor fetches pending events\n3. Calls `getSubscriptionsByEventType(eventType, projectId)`\n4. Calls `matchEvent(event, subscriptions)` for filtering\n5. Creates ExecRequests for matched subscriptions\n6. Dispatcher routes to available workers\n7. Workers execute and can emit new events\n\n**Multi-tenant Isolation:**\n- All major tables have project_id column\n- API routes enforce project_id on user requests\n- Subscription queries filter by projectId when provided\n\n### Summary\n\nThe codebase implements a clean event bus system with:\n- **Lightweight matching logic** in bus.ts (exact/wildcard sourceFilter matching)\n- **SQLite persistence** with better-sqlite3\n- **REST API** for subscription management\n- **Event processing loop** that runs every 2 seconds\n- **Project-scoped** subscriptions for multi-tenancy\n- **Concurrent execution** with persona-level concurrency limits\n\nNo test files were found in the codebase. All core logic is in the files listed above."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa701427022778fc5 (use SendMessage with to: 'aa701427022778fc5' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61957\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 60043</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"15915e67-0f08-45e6-a989-69b2c8df5088","uuid":"ec0b6b67-8794-45af-bcef-e2724ab67417","timestamp":"2026-03-18T18:51:12.352Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the codebase to understand:\n1. The bus.ts file - find it and read it entirely\n2. The subscription model/type definitions\n3. The `getSubscriptionsByEventType` function and how it works\n4. The `sourceFilterMatches` function and its prefix-matching logic\n5. Any database/storage layer for subscriptions (Drizzle schema, etc.)\n6. How subscriptions are created (API routes, etc.)\n7. Any test files related to bus or subscriptions\n\nSearch bro