riptions\n- `getSubscriptionsByEventType()` (lines 549-556): Retrieves subscriptions by event type\n- `listSubscriptionsForPersona()` (lines 544-547): Gets all subscriptions for a persona\n- `updateSubscription()` (lines 558-573): Updates subscription settings\n- `deleteSubscription()` (lines 575-577): Deletes a subscription\n\n### 5. **How Subscriptions Are Created - API Routes**\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/.claude/worktrees/idempotent-mapping-emerson/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts` (lines 160-177)\n\n**POST /api/subscriptions** (lines 160-164):\n- Creates new event subscription\n- Request body fields: personaId, eventType, sourceFilter (optional), enabled (default true), useCaseId (optional), projectId (auto-set for users)\n- Calls: `db.createSubscription(database, body)`\n- Returns: 201 with PersonaEventSubscription object\n\n**PUT /api/subscriptions/{id}** (lines 165-170):\n- Updates existing subscription\n- Request body: { eventType?, sourceFilter?, enabled? }\n- Calls: `db.updateSubscription(database, id, body)`\n- Returns: 200 with updated subscription\n\n**DELETE /api/subscriptions/{id}** (lines 171-174):\n- Deletes a subscription\n- Returns: 200 { deleted: true }\n\n**GET /api/personas/{id}/subscriptions** (lines 175-177):\n- Lists all subscriptions for a persona\n- Returns: 200 with array of subscriptions\n\n### 6. **Event Processing Flow**\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/.claude/worktrees/idempotent-mapping-emerson/packages/orchestrator/src/eventProcessor.ts`\n\n**startEventProcessor() (lines 16-31):**\n- Starts a 2-second tick interval (configurable, default 2000ms)\n- Calls eventBusTick() repeatedly\n\n**eventBusTick() (lines 33-123):**\nMain event processing loop:\n1. Fetches up to 50 pending events: `db.getPendingEvents(database, 50)`\n2. For each event:\n   - Marks event as 'processing'\n   - Gets subscriptions by event type: `db.getSubscriptionsByEventType(database, event.eventType, event.projectId)`\n   - Matches event to subscriptions: `matchEvent(event, subs)` (from bus.ts)\n   - For each match:\n     - Checks persona exists and is enabled\n     - Checks concurrency limits\n     - Parses event payload as JSON\n     - Assembles prompt from persona config and tools\n     - Creates ExecRequest and submits to dispatcher\n   - Updates event status: delivered/partial/failed/skipped\n\n### 7. **File Structure & Packages**\n\n**@dac-cloud/shared** - Shared types and utilities:\n- `bus.ts`: Event matching engine\n- `types.ts`: Domain type definitions\n- `protocol.ts`: WebSocket protocol between orchestrator and workers\n- `prompt.ts`: Prompt assembly for personas\n- `crypto.ts`: Encryption utilities\n\n**@dac-cloud/orchestrator** - Main orchestration service:\n- `index.ts`: Main entry point, starts all services\n- `db.ts`: SQLite database layer with schema and CRUD operations\n- `eventProcessor.ts`: Event bus tick loop\n- `dispatcher.ts`: Execution queuing and worker pool coordination\n- `httpApi.ts`: HTTP REST API server\n- `workerPool.ts`: WebSocket pool for worker processes\n- `kafka.ts`: Kafka client for event streaming\n- `tokenManager.ts`: Claude API token management\n- `oauth.ts`: OAuth flow for Anthropic subscriptions\n- `auth.ts`: Request authentication\n- `triggerScheduler.ts`: Scheduled trigger execution\n\n**@dac-cloud/worker** - Worker processes:\n- Executes persona prompts via Claude\n- Emits events back to orchestrator\n\n### 8. **Event Lifecycle**\n\n1. **Event Creation**: POST /api/events creates event with status='pending'\n2. **Event Processing**: eventBusTick picks up pending events every 2 seconds\n3. **Subscription Matching**: Gets subscriptions by eventType, filters by sourceFilter\n4. **Execution Dispatch**: Creates ExecRequest for each matched subscription\n5. **Status Updates**: Event status becomes delivered/partial/failed/skipped\n6. **Event Consumption**: Workers can emit events that cycle back through the system\n\n### 9. **Key Integration Points**\n\n**Event → Subscription Matching Chain:**\n1. Event arrives via API or Kafka (persona.events.v1 topic)\n2. eventProcessor fetches pending events\n3. Calls `getSubscriptionsByEventType(eventType, projectId)`\n4. Calls `matchEvent(event, subscriptions)` for filtering\n5. Creates ExecRequests for matched subscriptions\n6. Dispatcher routes to available workers\n7. Workers execute and can emit new events\n\n**Multi-tenant Isolation:**\n- All major tables have project_id column\n- API routes enforce project_id on user requests\n- Subscription queries filter by projectId when provided\n\n### Summary\n\nThe codebase implements a clean event bus system with:\n- **Lightweight matching logic** in bus.ts (exact/wildcard sourceFilter matching)\n- **SQLite persistence** with better-sqlite3\n- **REST API** for subscription management\n- **Event processing loop** that runs every 2 seconds\n- **Project-scoped** subscriptions for multi-tenancy\n- **Concurrent execution** with persona-level concurrency limits\n\nNo test files were found in the codebase. All core logic is in the files listed above."}],"totalDurationMs":60043,"totalTokens":61957,"totalToolUseCount":23,"usage":{"input_tokens":408,"cache_creation_input_tokens":389,"cache_read_input_tokens":58704,"output_tokens":2456,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":389},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
